# Commit Message Rules

When generating Git commit messages, always follow the format below.

## Format

```text
<type>: <Korean description>
```

## Types

- Feat: Add a new feature
- Fix: Fix a bug
- Docs: Documentation changes
- Style: Code style changes (formatting, semicolons, etc.)
- Refactor: Refactoring (no functional changes)
- Test: Add or update tests
- Chore: Build, config, or tooling changes
- Perf: Performance improvements

## Rules

1. Only the first letter of the type is uppercase (PascalCase)
2. Description must be concise in Korean (50 characters or less)
3. Do not start with English verbs such as "Add", "Update", or "Fix"
4. Do not use a period (`.`)
5. Write in present tense

## Examples

✅ Valid examples:

- `Feat: 소셜 로그인 기능 추가`
- `Fix: 사용자 조회 에러 수정`
- `Chore: 커밋 메시지 룰 추가`
- `Refactor: 공통 버튼 컴포넌트 분리`

❌ Invalid examples:

- `Add 소셜 로그인` (starts with English verb, no type)
- `Update 설정 파일` (starts with English verb, no type)
- `Feat: 로그인.` (contains period)
- `FEAT: 로그인` (all uppercase)